[325.756248, "o", "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - **Bug**: `eval_metric=\"rmse\"` was passed to `XGBClassifier`.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - **Why it is wrong**: RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error) is a regression metric. For binary \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   classification tasks—especially highly imbalanced ones like fraud detection—using a \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   regression loss/evaluation metric is inappropriate and misaligns the model training \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   and early stopping with the true target metric (AUC or Logloss).\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - **How it was fixed**: Changed the evaluation metric to `eval_metric=\"auc\"` to align \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   directly with the classification objective.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> --------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> 4. Loss of Signal from Dropping High-Value Categorical Features\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.756392, "o", "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.756524, "o", "- **Bug**: High-value categorical columns (`ProductCD`, `card4`, and `card6`) were \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[325.75654, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.756798, "o", "  dropped entirely from the feature set.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - **Why it is wrong**: Categorical features like product type (`ProductCD`), card issuer \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   network (`card4`), and card type (`card6` - credit vs. debit) contain crucial \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.757009, "o", "  discriminative signal for fraud detection. Removing them hurts model performance.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.757087, "o", "- **How it was fixed**: We kept these features in the pipeline, cast them to pandas \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[325.757273, "o", "  `category` dtype, and enabled native categorical feature support in XGBoost by setting \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   `enable_categorical=True`.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
